# 🛡️ PROJECT PROTECTION & FILE ORGANIZATION
- **ZERO ROOT CLUTTER**: Absolutely NO new files should be created in the project root directory.
- **MANDATORY DIRECTORIES**:
    - All source code and logic MUST go into `src/`.
    - All temporary files, test scripts, demos, or drafts MUST use the `browser_scratchpad_write` tool (stores in `.scratchpad/`).
    - All assets (images/CSS) MUST go into `src/static/`.
- **LEGACY CLEANUP**: Frequently check for and delete any `.ps1`, `.js`, or `.json` files that appear in the root unless they are `package.json` or `.env`.

# Browser Automation MCP Rules

Read `ARCHITECTURE.md` and `MCP_TOOL_GUIDE.md` first. These are the canonical references for this project.

- ---

> [!WARNING]
> **IMPORTANT FOR AI AGENTS**: 
> - **DO NOT USE CURL** to interact with this server. 
> - This is an **MCP STDIO** server. Use native tool calls only.
> - The port **1000** is ONLY for the optional management dashboard, NOT for tool execution.

---
- **Project Core**: This is a Node.js MCP server using Playwright. It is optimized for AI agents to perform stealthy browser actions.
- **Immediate Feedback**: ALWAYS use `embedImage: true` and `saveLocal: false` when taking screenshots; this ensures the image appears in the Cursor chat without creating junk files on the user's disk.
- **Selector Strategy**: Do not guess selectors. Use `browser_analyze` first to see interactive elements and their optimized selectors.
- **Performance**: Use `browser_fill_form` for forms instead of multiple `browser_type` calls.
- **Navigation**: Use `browser_open` for first-time visits and `browser_auto_explore` for discovering routes.
- **Stealth**: Do not simulate opening or clicking in text; use the real MCP tools.

Read implementation files only when editing or debugging the server itself.

- **CRITICAL CALLING RULE**: If you are calling tools via a wrapper like `use_mcp_tool`, you MUST pass the tool arguments inside a `nativeArgs` object (e.g., `nativeArgs: { "url": "..." }`). Failing to do this will cause execution errors.
- **CRITICAL RESOURCE RULE**: NEVER try to access executable tools as MCP resources by treating them as URIs (e.g. `mcp://browser-automation/browser_open` is INVALID). Tools like `browser_open` are executable actions, NOT read-only resources. Always call them as tools!
